SIMPLE: mandatary
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mandatary
<hw>Man"da*ta*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. mandatarius,
fr. <ets>mandatum</ets> a charge, commission, order: cf. F.
<ets>mandataire</ets>. See <er>Mandate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
to whom a command or charge is given; hence, specifically, a person to
whom the pope has, by his prerogative, given a mandate or order for his
benefice.</def> <rj><au>Ayliffe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who undertakes to discharge a
specific business commission; a mandatory.</def>
<rj><au>Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mandate</ent>⟦br⟧
